tip.text: Do try the pasta boutique stall. Good pasta n mains at a good price!
I am loving the concept, toast with matcha cream, free onsen egg and a cuppa latte, my kind of high tea

venue.name: TACHIHARA COFFEE タチハラコーヒー

tip.text: This is how my food was presented when it arrived at my table. I think I can cook better than this. Ridiculous ttm!
Loved the pulled pork taco n their burp burger! Excellent service as well. Will b back!
Overall given that the shop just opened, there is a lot of improvement to be done in terms of their service n food standard. Do give their milk tea a miss.
As seen on this photo, prawn aglio for $18.90RM is really not worth it so pls don't order unless really craving for pasta
Food was salty and definitely mediocre at best, not worth the money. Would only recommend people to go there for drinks.
Pizza was bad. Look at it! It is uncooked at the bottom n none of the staff bothered to check what's wrong with it. Never order their pizza!
Hougang muah Chee a must eat! Comes in peanut or black sesame. Yums!

formattedAddress: B1, Toa Payoh HDB Hub (480 Lor 6 Toa Payoh)

tip.text: Lemon curd n their classic creme brûlée is so nice! Must order! 10% discount if u download poket app. No gst!
Definitely the dark chocolate ice cream in a martini cup
Teh C was smooth n nice. Bread was nicely toasted with lightly spread kaya n butter. ups!
Serves good local Teh. :) do try

venue.name: North Bridge Road Market & Food Centre

tip.text: I recommend bangkok toast. The bread served here is soft n tasty. Must eat! Singapore sling tea has a unique taste, that doesn't reside well with me.
Teh terik was especially milky and the prata n curry generally sweet in taste. Definitely a lot of room needed to improve.

formattedAddress: 490 Toa Payoh Lor 6  #01-15 (Toa Payoh HDB Hub)

tip.text: Chen ji wanton mee stall!!! The combo of dumpling noodles plus their special spring roll is awesome! Light to eat, filled with taste. Highly recommended!
Love the malacca Teh n their version of pontian noodles. Well cooked, noodles were q and overall affordable. Do try it!
Bread was lightly toasted n kayu spread was not sweet. They even have Teh terik here! A must drink!
Live music here on sat night is good. Relaxing ambience n affordable pricing for alcoholic beverages. Highly recommended. :)
Could improve on their music volume, their chairs and music selection. Other than that, food portion n ingredients in their pasta is generous esp when it is only $10 after 10pm.
Chicken n mushroom waffles was alright, a little heavy after a few bites. It will be better if the waffles was more thick n crispy.

formattedAddress: Bishan - Ang Mo Kio Park (River Plains) (1382 Ang Mo Kio Ave 1)
location.address: Bishan - Ang Mo Kio Park (River Plains)

tip.text: Service is good n helpful. Seafood paella is good for 4 ladies with 10% discount. Every sat, all day happy hour. 20% Discount for food n drink! Things will b perfect if the place is non-smoking.

Penang Kia prawn noodle - not the best I have tasted. Only soup was flavorful. The young boss charged me $4 when I didn't specify $3 order but the bigger order still left me hungry. Much to b improved
I recommend zhi Xiang special lor mee #01-49 Very light n tasty. Ngoh Hiang n fish cake is flavorful. Only complaint is that it is very small portion.

venue.name: Blk 93 Lorong 4 Toa Payoh Market & Food Centre

tip.text: Service was helpful and sincere but could be a little more professional in the way that they took our orders. Food was amazingly good and affordable. I recommend the pulled pork sandwich!

All the food that were ordered were tasty and well presented. I recommend the aglio olio pasta and mushroom soup. Top off with green tea latte n hazelnut cake. Drink comes with free top-up of biscuits

location.state: กรุงเทพมหานคร
formattedAddress: กรุงเทพมหานคร 10110

tip.text: Other than the irritating houseflies, the almond tea is actually nice.
Good tasty lor mee! Love the fried fish n meat. Tasty!
Jia Cheng lor mee is quite nice. Do try.
The 2 wrinkled lemons served with my fish were inexcusable. Nevertheless, at least the food was served hot.
Feels that paying $3.30 for side dishes is way too ex. Is just veg or canned food.

venue.name: Qi Wei Ji Bao 奇味雞煲

tip.text: Braised pork goulash is a must try. Comfort food for the soul. 👍
Nice cosy ambience at this outlet. Try cold poached cake for dark chocolate lovers!
I don't recommend their black pepper crab. A little sweet for my liking. The salted egg crab was much better.
Overall, not my cup of tea. Food not fresh, mushroom soup tasted more like flour, marinara sauce tasted weird. Service wise can b alot better.
Do give amiss to the lemon meringue tart. Taste more like lemon jelly tart.
Ban mian! Super tasty

venue.name: West Coast Market Square (Market & Food Centre)

formattedAddress: #B1-K5 myVillage at Serangoon Garden (1 Maju Ave.)

tip.text: The kway chap at #01-21 is pretty nice. I know that meat ball doesn't go with kway chap but u should order anyway. Is nice!

venue.name: Jalan Bukit Merah Market & Hawker Centre

tip.text: Try their warm strawberry shortcake!! Delicious!!
Chocolate lava cake with pomme tea!!! Awesome

venue.name: Fish and Chips @ Café Wok Inn

tip.text: Brilliant food with the authenticity of Korean cuisine. Even side dishes tastes fresh and tasty. Must eat Ginseng chicken soup and kim chi fried rice. :)
I must agree that the nasi Lemak is not as good as before. Manage your expectations
Try the food at the jing hua la mian!! Fantastic
Tried the wild rocket burger to start, it was alright, had better burgers. Service was impeccable, attentive and full of service. Nice ambience. Will revisit

location.crossStreet: 501 Bukit Timah Rd (next to Serene Centre)
formattedAddress: #02-01, Cluny Court (501 Bukit Timah Rd (next to Serene Centre))
#03-12, Ang Mo Kio Hub (53 Ang Mo Kio Ave 3)

tip.text: Roasted chrispy chicken was very good. Crunching and juicy, not dry at all. Service was impeccable, attentive and courteous. A must come!
